      "content": "those are good starting points, but they're a bit generic for a competitive debate round. my students need more meat on the bones. could you go deeper into the specific philosophical and economic justifications? for example, can you expand on the 'national sovereignty' aspect and the arguments regarding the strain on social infrastructure or the labor market? i need them to be able to present these points with real depth and sophistication.",
